	<Title>
		Sunless tanning tips
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Want to avoid orange palms, knees and elbows when you&apos;re using sunless tanning products? Scrub your skin before you apply the sunless tanning product. Use a washcloth or a sponge to remove excess dead skin cells. Use less sunless tanner on dry or thickened skin, such as the skin over your ankles, knees and elbows. When you&apos;re done, wash your hands and clean under your fingernails. Then use a cotton ball to apply sunless tanner to the top of each hand.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
